onERC721Received(address,address,uint256.details: The ERC721 smart contract calls this function on the recipient  after a `transfer`. This function MAY throw to revert and reject the  transfer. Return of other than the magic value MUST result in the  transaction being reverted.  Note: the contract address is always the message sender.

params._data: Additional data with no specified format
params._from: The address which previously owned the token
params._tokenId: The NFT identifier which is being transferred

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

ItemCanceled(address,address,uint256).notice: Event emitted when an item listing is canceled

ItemListed(address,address,uint256,uint6.notice: Event emitted when a new item is listed

ItemRented(address,address,address,uint2.notice: Event emitted when an item is rented

ItemUpdated(address,address,uint256,uint.notice: Event emitted when an item listing is updated

ProceedsWithdrawn(address,address,uint25.notice: Event emitted when proceeds are withdrawn
